<p>Troy Flake spent years on the other side of the courtroom — first as an Assistant United States Attorney, then as a Trial Attorney for the Securities and Exchange Commission. He knows how the government builds cases because he built them. Now he uses that knowledge to fight for clients who need someone in their corner.</p>
<p>His practice focuses on personal injury, medical malpractice, FTCA/VA medical malpractice, and federal civil investigations. Troy handles the cases that require someone who isn't intimidated by federal agencies, hospital systems, or insurance companies.</p>
